main event: A CDC spotter saw a rocket-shaped object with flaming exhaust moving very fast over Hot Swell, VA on October 15, 1952.
interesting points: The object was described as rocket-shaped with flaming exhaust, indicating it may have been a jet or other advanced aircraft.
The object was observed moving at a very high speed.
The sighting was made by a CDC (Civil Defense) spotter, suggesting it may have been a military or government-related observation.
The report includes conclusions that the object was likely an aircraft, possibly a jet, or potentially an astronomical phenomenon.
No photographs were included with this report.
